 2017-12782017-10-25,  ,  ,  ,  GAC
PrecisAppointment of Julia Bentley as High Commissioner for Canada in Malaysia; Susan Bincoletto as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Principality of Liechtenstein, with residence in Bern; Nicholas Brousseau as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Kyrgyz Republic, with residence in Astana; Alexandra Bugailiskis as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Republic of Albania, with concurrent accreditation as High Commissioner for Canada in the Republic of Malta, with residence in Rome; Lilian Chatterjee as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Republic of Suriname, with residence in Georgetown; Hilary Childs-Adams as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the State of Libya; René Cremonese as High Commissioner for Canada in the Republic of Botswana, with residence in Harare; Kati Csaba as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Republic of Serbia, with concurrent accreditation as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to Montenegro and as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Republic of Macedonia, with residence in Belgrade; James Hill as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Republic of Costa Rica, with concurrent accreditation as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Republic of Nicaragua and as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Republic of Honduras, with residence in San José; Nathalie O’Neil as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Gabonese Republic, with residence in Yaoundé; Laurie Peters as High Commissioner for Canada in the Commonwealth of the Bahamas, with residence in Kingston; Nicolas Simard as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Republic of the Congo, with residence in Kinshasa; and Edmond Dejon Wega as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to Burkina Faso, with concurrent accreditation as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Republic of Benin, with residence in Ouagadougou.
